The paper deals with the problem of runtime enforcement in the context of synchronous programs, which are reactive systems. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as it deals with the design and development of software systems, including reactive systems. The paper also proposes a framework for monitoring and editing inputs/outputs, which involves programming language concepts such as syntax and semantics, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) a likely category as well. The paper also involves logical reasoning and proof of correctness, which falls under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper deals with safety-critical systems, which may involve security concerns, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with synchronous programming, which is a specific type of reactive programming, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category as well.
